column1: # Name: Median age at first marriage, female, highest income quintile

# Definition: The median age at first marriage is the median age of women at first marriage if subject throughout their lives to the age-specific marriage rates of first marriages only in a given year (ages 25-49), by household wealth index
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
